data.description: Your chance to grab this one...Inspections done with a couple of minor items and the buyer walked. So...let's talk!   One level living with NO HOA or Restrictions (only County regulated restrictions) tucked between Sherman Oaks and Lovell Landing. The long concrete driveway leads you back to the semi hidden property that sits back off of Lovell Rd. This one has it ALL ready for YOU' to move right on in. The additional building can be a workshop, man cave, she shack, office separate from the home or living quarters for parent/child/guests... you name it. The RV shelter has all the hookups for use on site. Home has been Freshly painted in the color 'Toasted Gray'  creating a blank canvas for its new owners. The Cathedral ceiling in the living room creates added space to the open concept with the kitchen and dine in area. The Trey Ceiling in the formal dining room, at the entry, gives it  a grand feel. Bonus room over the garage is a true bonus! Oh, Master bedroom also has a cathedral ceiling. Enjoy the Sunroom year round and the patio with the pergola/cover every chance you can.  Home is surrounded by a wooden privacy fence and the Yard at the home/building is fenced in for kiddos and fur babies.  Owners had the home built with lots of care and details and are ready to pass it on to the next fortunate homeowners. Oh and shopping is so convenient...Turkey Creek shopping and I-40 are  just minutes away!  Hardin Valley Schools also make this home a great choice.  Call ASAP for your private showing.
